A group of young Nigerians under the “l am Nigeria” initiative have vowed to get 5,000 residents of Kaduna State registered in the ongoing Permanent Voters Card (PVC) registration in the state. The group, which commenced a PVC campaign in Kaduna at the weekend, said at least 300 prospective voters have been registered at the commencement of its campaign and vowed to extend the campaign to other states across the country. Speaking with Daily Trust, the Executive Director of “I am Nigeria,” Julius Denham, said for Nigeria to work, the citizens must play a part and urged the youths to build a Nigeria of their dream. From Edward Ojile, Kaduna